column3: Waterbody ID(WBIC)
Secchi (Feet)
Depth Units

column2: For all sample dates in 2005- disk is visible until it sinks into the muck which is very deep in places.  Loose material comes up with disk.  Water level is 2+ feet lower than normal.
Water is clear to muck were secchi sinks in.  Weeds are emerging with more than normal density.
Weeds cover most of lake area except for a few deep and very mucky spots.
Water level is extremely low- probably 3 to 4 feet lower than normal.  Some piers are out of the water completely.
Low water level  - down about 4 feet
Water level is up 3.5 to 4 feet which is back to normal levels for spring.
Windy weather recently.  Large algae blooms apparent which are extremely rare for this lake
Algae blooms continue.  Water clarity varies from area to area.  Where blooms are prominent- visibility is reduced to several feet.  Secchi ranged from 3 feet to 8 feet.
Lake cleared up and is very clear once again.  Some areas had algae scum along shore or under boats that were in the water.

Lots of floating plants and scummy stuff in globs that break up if you try to scoop them up.  Appears to be an algae of sorts that clings to the floating plants.  Many people did not want to swim in it.  However- the water was clear.
Lake has stayed very clear most of the summer.  Actually unusually clear.  Lots of minnows- pollywogs- blue gill and bass.  Significant drop in lake level in the last month.
Lots of floating pine pollen and weeds but clarity is good
Swimmers itch on several people this weekend
Lots of floating weed masses and clumps of what appear to be filamentous algae.  Some reports of swimmers itch around July 4th.
Lots of floating weeds and algae (filamentous )
Getting slightly better but still yucky.  This has been the worst stretch of bad water observed on the lake since monitoring
Weeds are low. No minnows or bluegill seen
Unusually hot and dry.  Water level dropped significantly
Ice off.  water level low.  clear water
suspended particles.  lots of floating pollen and globs of algae
some algae globs but much fewer
some suspended algae and small particles after significant rain
algae seems to have settled out and cleared
Lowest water level in spring in many years
Lots of floating globs of algae and plant gook (yes that is the scientific name I believe)
Water level has been fairly steady and would not be more normal for mid summer but still low.  Water is crystal clear

Lake has been outstandingly clear all summer except for a short period the end of May.  Lake weeds are low and bottom is bare in large areas.  Large leaf pond weed is low with only some plants reaching the surface and not looking vibrant as in previous years.  Some clumps of what appear to be niaid are up.  Cattails are still back along shore but have not re-emerged much into the water.  Water lilies have taken residence where cattails used to be.
Lots of weeds- some suspended algae
suspended algae and some filamentous algae
